.SH NAME
longjmp \- non-local goto
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
\fB#include <setjmp.h>
.br
.sp
void longjmp(jmp_buf\fP \fIenv\fP\fB, int\fP \fIval\fP\fB);
.br
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIlongjmp\fP() function shall restore tha environment saved by
da most thugged-out recent invocation of \fIsetjmp\fP() up in tha same thread, with
the correspondin \fBjmp_buf\fP argument. If there is no
such invocation, or if tha function containin tha invocation of \fIsetjmp\fP()
has
terminated execution up in tha interim, or if tha invocation of \fIsetjmp\fP()
was within the
scope of a identifier wit variably modified type n' execution has
left dat scope up in tha interim, tha behavior is undefined.
\ It be unspecified whether \fIlongjmp\fP() restores tha signal mask,
leaves tha signal mask unchanged, or restores it ta its
value all up in tha time \fIsetjmp\fP() was called. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! 
.LP
All accessible objects have joints, n' all other componentz of the
abstract machine have state (for example, floating-point
status flags n' open files), az of tha time \fIlongjmp\fP() was called,
except dat tha jointz of objectz of automatic storage
duration is unspecified if they hook up all tha followin conditions:
.IP " *" 3
They is local ta tha function containin tha correspondin \fIsetjmp\fP()
invocation.
.LP
.IP " *" 3
They aint gots volatile-qualified type.
.LP
.IP " *" 3
They is chizzled between tha \fIsetjmp\fP() invocation n' \fIlongjmp\fP()
call.
.LP
.LP
As
it bypasses tha usual function call n' return mechanisms, \fIlongjmp\fP()
shall execute erectly up in contextz of interrupts,
signals, n' any of they associated functions. But fuck dat shiznit yo, tha word on tha street is dat if \fIlongjmp\fP()
is invoked from a nested signal handlez (that is, from
a function invoked as a result of a signal raised durin tha handling
of another signal), tha behavior is undefined.
.LP
Da effect of a cold-ass lil call ta \fIlongjmp\fP() where initialization of the
\fBjmp_buf\fP structure was not performed up in tha calling
thread is undefined. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! 
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
Afta \fIlongjmp\fP() is completed, program execution continues as
if tha correspondin invocation of \fIsetjmp\fP() had just returned
the value specified by \fIval\fP. Da \fIlongjmp\fP() function
shall not cause \fIsetjmp\fP() ta return 0; if \fIval\fP is 0, \fIsetjmp\fP()
shall return 1.
.SH ERRORS
.LP
No errors is defined.
.LP
\fIDa followin sections is informative.\fP
